  <main id="top">
    <section class="section details-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Complete Product Information</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          This page summarizes the app structure and major functionality across authentication, planning, itinerary,
          social interaction, account management, notifications, premium features, legal pages, and admin operations.
        </p>
        <div class="badge-row">
          <span class="badge">React Native + Expo Router</span>
          <span class="badge">AI Trip Planning</span>
          <span class="badge">Zelo Social Meetups</span>
          <span class="badge">Cloud-backed Accounts</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="modules" class="section section-soft">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Main Application Modules</h2>
        <div class="module-grid">
          <article class="module-card">
            <h3>Authentication</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Welcome, login, register, forgot-password, and auth callbacks.</li>
              <li>Role-aware redirects and authenticated main flow access.</li>
              <li>Zelo profile onboarding steps integrated into auth lifecycle.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="module-card">
            <h3>Questionnaire & Planning</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Destination search with validation and fallback list-city support.</li>
              <li>Dates, budget, interests, and traveler/person configuration.</li>
              <li>Generating flow followed by itinerary result screens.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="module-card">
            <h3>Main App Screens</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Trip details, to-do management, saved trips, and travel preferences.</li>
              <li>Profile, privacy settings, security, feedback, and help pages.</li>
              <li>Notifications and account-related utilities.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="module-card">
            <h3>Social Layer (Zelo)</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Create or join map-based intent places with date/time and location.</li>
              <li>Participant visibility and in-place chat coordination.</li>
              <li>Token-oriented listing/joining model and premium plan entry points.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="module-card">
            <h3>Monetization & Premium</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Token plan screens and premium subscription UI pathways.</li>
              <li>In-app purchase integration readiness in project documentation.</li>
              <li>Admin notification hooks for subscription intent workflows.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="module-card">
            <h3>Admin & Operations</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>User management, verification requests, and admin notifications.</li>
              <li>Security events and admin development tools screens.</li>
              <li>Database-backed policies and migration-driven feature evolution.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="flows" class="section">
      <div class="container split">
        <article class="info-box">
          <h3>User Journey Coverage</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Entry: auth gate checks profile/session and redirects accordingly.</li>
            <li>Planning: questionnaire captures trip intent and preferences.</li>
            <li>Generation: app builds itinerary recommendations from integrated services.</li>
            <li>Execution: users review trip cards, revisit saved items, and manage details.</li>
            <li>Social: users open Zelo for nearby intent-based interactions and chat.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="info-box">
          <h3>Account, Privacy, and Legal</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Dedicated screens for account settings and privacy/security controls.</li>
            <li>Notification settings and communication preferences management.</li>
            <li>Standalone web pages for privacy policy, terms, and attributions.</li>
            <li>Support contact path via in-app help and public email channel.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="social" class="section section-soft">
      <div class="container split">
        <article class="info-box">
          <h3>Zelo Capabilities</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Intent-first meetup creation linked to map locations.</li>
            <li>Discovery of existing places and participant interactions.</li>
            <li>Chat for planning and real-time coordination with joined users.</li>
            <li>Safety-minded moderation and notification-enabled communication.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="info-box">
          <h3>Tokens and Purchase Readiness</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Token plans support expanded listing and joining activity.</li>
            <li>Premium and token flows are surfaced in dedicated app screens.</li>
            <li>IAP setup guidance exists for both iOS and Android app stores.</li>
            <li>Cloud-backed account data keeps user states synced across sessions.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="platform" class="section">
      <div class="container two-col">
        <div>
          <h2>Tech and Integration Footprint</h2>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li>Location intelligence and search powered through map/location APIs.</li>
            <li>AI support for personalized itinerary logic and recommendation output.</li>
            <li>Webhook workflow support for planning and processing operations.</li>
            <li>Cloud services for authentication, persistence, and real-time interactions.</li>
            <li>Large route and migration set supporting continuous product expansion.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
